xyz \neq 0
 x \ln 2 = y \ln 3 = (2z) (- \ln 6) 
\frac{ 1}{x} \left( 1 + \frac{ \ln 3} { \ln 2}  - \frac{ \ln 6} { \ln 2} \right) = \quad ??
2^x=3^y=36^{-z}=k\implies x=\frac{\ln k}{\ln 2},y=\frac{\ln k}{\ln 3}
z=-\frac{\ln k}{\ln 36}
\frac{1}{x}+\frac{1}{y}+\frac{1}{2z}=\frac{\ln 2}{\ln k}+\frac{\ln 3}{\ln k}-\frac{\ln 36}{2\ln k}=\frac{\ln4+\ln 9-\ln 36}{2\ln k}=\frac{\ln 36-\ln 36}{2\ln k}=0
